 The train driver told the police that he saw a man attempting to cross the railway line behind the Nkangala District Municipality offices. In a joint effort to find the man, the officials searched for him in the open fields however, they could not find any trace of him. No sign of fatality. When Transnet officials examined the train they found red spots that looked like blood. Transnet officials are visiting hospitals to look for the man.     Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za